-- Idea to Plan — full pipeline from vague idea to approved beads.
-- Demonstrates: sub-molecule invocation, human gates, convoy composition.
--
-- Pipeline: intake → prd-review (convoy) → human-clarify →
--           generate-plan (convoy) → plan-review (convoy) →
--           human-approve → create-beads

## idea-to-plan

  input param.problem : str required
  input param.context : str default("")

  # intake : llm
    system>
      You are a product manager structuring vague ideas into PRDs.
    user>
      The user described this idea:
      {{param.problem}}

      Additional context:
      {{param.context}}

      Structure it into a draft PRD with:
      - Problem statement
      - Success criteria
      - Scope (in/out)
      - Key requirements
      - Open questions
    format> prd
      {
        problem: str,
        success_criteria: [str],
        scope_in: [str],
        scope_out: [str],
        requirements: [str],
        open_questions: [str]
      }
  #/

  -- Sub-molecule: 6 polecats review PRD in parallel
  # prd-review : mol(mol-prd-review)
    - intake
    vars>
      prd = {{intake}}
  #/

  -- Human gate: agent presents questions, user answers
  # human-clarify : llm
    - prd-review
    system>
      You are facilitating a conversation between the PRD review
      findings and the original requester.
    context>
      Original idea: {{param.problem}}
      PRD review findings: {{prd-review}}
    user>
      Present the consolidated questions and gaps from the PRD review.
      Ask the user for clarification on each open question.
      Incorporate their answers into a refined PRD.
    accept>
      All critical questions answered. Refined PRD ready.
  #/

  -- Sub-molecule: 6 polecats design the implementation in parallel
  # generate-plan : mol(design)
    - human-clarify
    vars>
      problem = {{human-clarify}}
      context = {{param.context}}
  #/

  -- Sub-molecule: 5 polecats review the plan
  # plan-review : mol(mol-plan-review)
    - generate-plan
    vars>
      plan = {{generate-plan}}
  #/

  -- Human gate: approve or reject
  # human-approve : decision
    - plan-review
    system>
      You are presenting an implementation plan for approval.
    context>
      Plan: {{generate-plan}}
      Review: {{plan-review}}
    user>
      Present the plan review verdict.
      If the plan passes review, recommend approval.
      If it has critical issues, recommend revision.
    format> verdict
      { approved: "true" | "false", conditions: [str], blockers: [str] }

    ```oracle
    json_parse(output);
    keys_present(output, ["approved"]);
    ```
  #/

  -- Create beads from approved plan
  # create-beads : script
    - human-approve
    ```bash
    if [ "{{human-approve.approved}}" != "true" ]; then
      echo "Plan not approved. Blockers: {{human-approve.blockers}}"
      exit 1
    fi
    echo "Creating beads from approved plan..."
    # The agent reads generate-plan output and creates bd issues
    echo "beads_created=true"
    ```

    ```oracle
    assert output contains "beads_created=true";
    ```
  #/

  squash> trigger: on_complete template: plan include_metrics: true

##/
